17 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
18 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
19 Article – Natural Resources
20 10–301.1.
21 (a) (1) (i) On or after July 1, 1977, a person under 18 years of age may not
22 procure a hunting license or hunt in the State, unless the person has first been issued a
23 certificate of competency in firearms and hunter safety.
