5 (2) (i) This section does not apply to nonresidents of Maryland who
6 purchase a nonresident 3–day hunting license in the State to hunt wild waterfowl.
7 (ii) This section applies to nonresidents of Maryland who purchase
8 hunting licenses in the State to hunt wildlife other than wild waterfowl.
9 (b) (1) The Department shall prescribe a course of instruction in conservation
10 and in competency and safety in the handling of firearms.
11 (2) (i) The Department shall designate those persons or agencies
12 authorized to give the course of instruction, and this designation shall be valid until
13 revoked by the Department.
14 (ii) Those designated persons shall submit to the Department
15 validated listings naming all persons who have successfully completed the course of
16 instruction.
17 (3) (I) The Department shall issue [a certificate of competency and
18 safety] to each person who successfully completes the course of instruction[, and the
19 certificate]:
20 1. A CERTIFICATE OF COMPETENCY AND SAFETY; AND
21 2. A PERMANENT IDENTIFICATION NUMBER.
22 (II) A CERTIFICATE OF COMPETENCY AND SAFETY ISSUED
23 UNDER THIS PARAGRAPH shall be valid until revoked by the Department.
24 (III) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL PRINT THE PERMANENT
25 IDENTIFICATION NUMBER ASSIGNED TO A PERSON UNDER THIS PARAGRAPH ON:
26 1. THE CERTIFICATE OF COMPETENCY AND SAFETY
27 ISSUED TO THE PERSON; OR
28 2. A SEPARATE FORM PROVIDED WITH THE
29 CERTIFICATE OF COMPETENCY AND SAFETY.
30 (4) The Department may not issue a certificate of competency and safety to
31 an individual under the age of 18 unless the individual has completed satisfactorily the

